reviews: Perfect location for our needs, we needed an hotel near Gare du Nord station and this one is at a perfect walking distance. The facilities are overall good , and I would like to extend my thanks to Mary at reception for taking really good care of us.

Nice hotel at great location. Metro station just outside of the hotel.
Coffee and tea available at all times free of charge.
Family room with one double bed and one couch bed. Bed was great, couch bed was acceptable. Bathroom large clean and well maintained. Housekeeping changed towels and cleaned the room every day.
Breakfast was below average. Not enough of selection or quantity. Better get something from the near convenience store.
Practically no English from one of the receptionists. No way to answer questions or give instructions. The other one I’ve met was helpful polite and knowledgeable. Overall great experience with a few minor negatives.

we had a very good staying in your hotel. nice room, good bearkfast and 2 steps from the metro. nights were too hot because of central heating, your adviced to open the window was funny. Thank you for your help and advices for the trasportaion from Disny at the strike. we hope to come back soon.

I had to book my stay last minute, but I was surprised that I got a great deal in terms of cost.

The star were multilingual too so another couple were so happy to be helped in English.

I'll definitely be back soon.

We were extremely pleased with the room - in spite of its "tight" quarters. The water pressure and water temp was great for showering. We forgot (misplaced) an outlet plug. We were pleased we were able to "borrow" the necessary plug from the front desk!

I enjoyed staying there, everything is so close to the hotel. My husband loved the fresh croissants, i loved the eggs and sausages. Moreover the service is impeccable, from the breakfast lady to the receptionists.

We enjoyed our stay very much, everything is close and the location is quiet. Me and my husband didn’t regret our choice, thank you for everything, the ladies at the reception have been wonderful with us!

The hotel staff was very friendly.
The room was a little small.
The hygiene was very good.
During the night it was too warm in the room.
The staff was willing to help you and to speak English.
The hotel was near the metro.

The room felt both new and clean, breakfast was good, location was convenient to business meetings and tourist areas, and the hotel team was very friendly and helpful. I would definitely stay here again if I have a return trip to Paris.

Bed was really comfy and service was good. We were not able to check in earlier but were able to leave our bags there whilst we explored and come back later. Lots of space for clothing in the cupboards which we liked.
Hairdryer cord was far too short to dry long hair - better off taking your own. Shower doors didn’t close properly so floor got wet outside. Items in the mini fridge - it wasn’t made clear whether these were complementary or not. There were no prices on them so we drank some of the drinks and was billed for them at check out. Also went to breakfast about 10am (finishes 10:30) and none of the food or juices were replenished so there was unfortunately not much to choose from.

Great hotel with Excellent service. Close to the Metro. Close to everything. The Staff are very friendly and helpful. Make you feel welcome!
It feels safe to walk around even late at night. We strongly recommenced , a great place to stay in Paris!

Excellent stay, very convenient location, very friendly and responsive front desk staff and dining staff. Close to Gare du Nord and metro. Well kept rooms and friendly staff. Highly recommend for families.

When you travel with family you expect everything to be ok and without any problem. The front desk staff was extremely helpful when we arrive. The breakfast buffet had a alot of variety, even for a gluten free diet.

We really enjoyed our stay in this beautiful hotel. All staff is amazing, everybody is always smiling and kind! The breakfast is excellent with a large choice of salty and sweet. We’ll definitely come back!

We really enjoyed our stay here. The room had plenty of space for a family of 3 including a great bathtub and separate shower with a rainfall shower head. The beds were comfy and the rooms were clean. The staff were all extremely friendly and helpful. The location was great- steps away from a metro station and in a really neat neighborhood- not touristy, great food options, yet with easy access to any part of the city. We really enjoyed it and would absolutely recommend this location.

This small hotel is perfect for those arriving late or leaving early from Gare du Nord as it's an easy walk from the station. My room was small but well equipped (kettle and a coffee machine, laptop safe, folding table, etc), and there was a small breakfast room next to reception. With a large window onto an internal courtyard, the room was quiet. I shall return in the summer as the hotel has a small outdoor courtyard space with chairs! The staff were friendly and helpful, and I shall definitely be back.

Good hotel and very nice decoration. My room was big and very very clean. For a solo trip is the best choice because there’s a warm atmosphere thank to the nice and kind staff, always professional and friendly. They gave me really good parisian tips!

We only stayed one night, after an awful experience in a nearby Airbnb. The lady on reception knew I was coming and was always helpful. The room was a great size and had a nice quirky vibe, with a massive comfy king size bed and decent soundproofing - which is needed for the centre of Paris.

Loved it. I'll most likely stay again

Very good hotel and staff. The hotel is located a few meters from a metro station. Staff very receptive and friendly. I advise very strongly. We like the cleanliness of the property, and the breakfast is really complete.

It was awesome. I’ve been here with my family and they treated us wonderfully. The place is very clean and comfortable, I couldn’t have made a better choice as it’s also very close to many attractions. Thank you! We will be back 😃

The staff was super friendly, the hotel is extremely clean and the rooms are impeccable with very comfortable beds. Breakfast was very nice with many options. The metro entrance is just 50 meters from the hotel. Definitely will come back.

The location is good near metro station. The room is comfortable but the bathroom is on a separate floor and very strange staircase
There was a smoking area outside the room and people were sitting and chatting till late at night. Late check in 3 pm

Hotel well located and nicely decorated. The staff is polite and professional they helped me with everything from the culture trips to the restaurants tours. The room was nice and very clean. Me and my family made an excellent choice.

Racist to Asians, very rude stuff. Disappointed. Never go there if you are Asian, if you don't want to be treated unfair. We will never choose Best western hotel anymore. One of the worst experience of my life.

I was a good surprise, i small hotel but with good facilities. Bed super confortable and big. Also the bathroom. The only negative thing is the breakfast, we were missing some fresh fruit pieces and vegetal milk

This is a very convenient place for business or pleasure, walking distance from the train station, with nice places to eat and drink nearby. The staff is friendly and willing to help with everything. The place, unlike many other hotels in Paris, is clean and very neat.

Vera Good stay! Nice staff too!
First trip to Paris and I was really good. The hotel is well located, near to the subway with many restaurants around the area and places to visit.
Definitely a place to come back.

I spent a lovely stay in this hotel.
The room was clean and well decorated and the receptionist nice and welcoming.
Breakfast is a plus, I loved the fresh fruits and local croissants.
I will definitely come back again!

Couldn’t fault this hotel at all. Great staff. Lovely clean room. Extremely comfy bed. Would definitely consider staying here again if I visit Paris in the future. We paid extra for the slightly bigger room and was definitely worth it.

Perfect location (very close to the metro and gare du nord) , and a very nice room. The internet is fast enough and the air condition is helpful in summer. The people at reception and breakfast were very friendly and helpful. I will come back definitely. Thank you so much!

Three nights here and we had a lovely time. Lovely clean room. Big enough and the bed was so comfy. The staff were fantastic. Particularly Charles who looked after us very well and gave us great recommendations. All staff worked so hard. Thank you

The room was super clean, however there was no space around the King size bed. It was essentially a bed with four walls around it. Not a lot of room to move around. The hotel does not have a lounge to chat with other friends who were staying at the hotel. Very very clean. But Very very small.

Very cute room, it was shared between 3 adults, they were accommodating with this request, bathroom was spacious, clean room, front desk staff was helpful, no issues with check in or out, and someone was always there in the evening. The main door locks during late evening hours for safety, I appreciated this.
Enjoyed the location, not a tourist trap area, cute local restaurants close by, supermarket and bakery close by, and metro is right there so we can head anywhere. There was some construction down the block, but we did not hear it. Thank you for the visit.

The hotel was just ok. The rooms are small and when we booked the executive room for 3 we expected a connecting rooms but this particular hotel doesn’t have that option. So 3 of us in a small room. 2 adults, 1 child. The fold-out bed was uncomfortable & right up against the door and blocking access to the wardrobe/tea making facilities. We were only there for 1 night but wouldn’t want to stay there for longer in this particular room.

The staff were friendly and helpful and made up for the room situation.

The hotel was fantastic
wonderful staff especially Charles
I had a great stay with my friends it was a parisean summer midnight dream
Rooms are clean , comfortable, service is high top qualty and staff as well
Thanks to all
Definetly will come back

Unfortunately, Our stay was bad. We came to our room to find sh** in the toilet&opened drink in mini bar. The toilet seemed like it was clogged and we were afraid to use it and went to another bathroom downstairs. We got a sorry&free breakfast. For almost €400/night and a 4-star hotel it's unacceptable. The breakfast attendant was very nice, she gets the one star rating.
I was asked to submit the pictures of the nasty toilet…. Ok.

Very much enjoyed our stay because of the friendly and helpful staff, comfortable rooms, and convenient location. Affordable place to stay. Quiet and lovely courtyard to sit in. We arrived early and the staff kindly stored our luggage until check in.

Great location within 6 minutes walking distance of Gare du Nord. The room was very clean, the bed was incredibly comfortable. We were let down badly by another hotel and this hotel looked after us perfectly at the last minute. Staff were so kind & friendly too. Highly recommended.

Having booked through booking.com 6 months previous, the hotel cancelled our booking on the day. This was because of their system error. Caused major hassle. Avoid like the plague. Not willing to help

Great location within walking distance of Gare du Nord. No complaints about the room and the space available - there was both a bath and a shower . Bed is incredibly comfortable. Breakfast offered both hot and cold options. I felt that the room rate was good value .Staff were friendly and engaging. Already planning my next visit.

great place to stay. very nice stuff. they helped us with everything. newly renovated. central location at the metro. restaurants all around. absolut to recommend. next visit to paris we will come again.

I spent 2 nights in the hotel and the overall experience waa very good. The hotel is well located, just in front of one metro station and has a lot of servicies in the area. The staff was very professional, kind and treated us very well.

The hotel was in a good location for public transport links, supermarkets and restaurants. Room was comfortable with a good shower and a useful kettle. The breakfasts were excellent and the staff were friendly and helpful.

We stayed recently during our family visit to Paris.
There are was a mistake by me while booking, but Nadiya & Elina very promptly suggested changes and accommodated us.
Post my marathon event Hyo, lady on the reception allowed the luggage to be kept & gave us access to freshen-up.
Good location & friendly staff.

My boyfriend and I stayed at the Best Western Premier Faubourg 88 on the night of the 18th of December 2021, and we both had to shower in cold water. That is inadmissible!
When booking a room in any Hotel the least one expects and, what we paid for, are clean sheets, complete breakfast, and a hot shower. But, unbelievably, the latter requirement wasn’t met, which meant for us having to shower in freezing water in mid-December. This is unacceptable and outrageous for any hotel, let alone one with 4 starts and belonging to the Best Western chain.

During the check-out, we alerted the receptionist for the matter in question and we were told that all guests were facing the same issue and that this has been a recurrent problem for at least a full-on week. That means that the hotel is letting guests book a room in the establishment fully aware that there isn’t enough warm water and don’t even have the decency to warn them about the issue during the reservation or the check-in. A bad decision on top of a terrible situation!

Booked a room 2 years ahead of time and had to reschedule our trip due to covid. the booking was changed to June 2021 and we received a confirmation that our room was reserved. so, I get to the hotel at 10am on Saturday, its about to rain, got my wife in a wheelchair, kids, luggage, no cell phone service yet, and walked from Gare due Nord to the faubourg, and they are closed. just a sign that we should call or email. so, the number went to voicemail and no reply from the email. thankfully, a competent and caring hotel, the Best Western Anjou, was able to call and get us a nice room right on the spot. I would generally not give a rating such as this, but I think for leaving me literally in the rain with no hotel, this should allow 0/5 stars. DO NOT BOOK OR STAY HERE. IF THEY ARE WILLING TO LEAVE YOU OUT IN THE RAIN WITH NO NOTICE AND STILL TAKE YOUR MONEY WHO KNOWS WHAT ELSE THEY ARE WILLING TO DO.

It's a rather nice hotel in a nice location right by the métro. The room looked quite nice, the shower was great and so was the bed. It wasn't noisy at all which is quite something for a hotel in Paris.

N'a pas aimé · However, the rooms are TINY! The bed takes list if the room and we had to put a chair in the wardrobe to create a bit of space. That's the only issue, really. But I felt it was a bit expensive for such a small room.

We stayed here on Sunday 19th July and before deciding to write this review I emailed the business to detail the issues I had: I’ve not had a reply.

We booked a double, non-smoking, room for 1 night. On arrival we checked in and were given room 003. Despite the fact that no facilities were open in the hotel (not a problem I do understand Covid19 restrictions) we were asked to provide a credit card for 50 euro pre-approval for spend whilst there.... really? ... process above service quality I would say.

It was a hot day so when we went to our room I tried to switch on the air-conditioning (remember 4 star hotel) and it was not working so went to reception. They advised they were aware of the issue and would call the engineer on Monday as it was too expensive to call out an engineer on a Sunday. I asked if we could change room and was advised it was an issue with all rooms and the hotel was full so no we couldn’t change rooms.

I then noticed that despite having booked a non-smoking room the room given was in the centre of the smoking area with ingress and regress from the room requiring a walk through the smoking area. It also meant we couldn’t open the room window to alleviate the non-working air-conditioning issue as the rancid and discussing smoke from the constant stream of smokers outside would waft in.

We slept on top of the bed completely unclothed but it was still so warm we could not sleep. In total I had about 2 hours sleep. What good a hotel if you cannot have a good nights sleep.

All-in-all I would avoid avoid avoid. This hotel is only interested in YOUR money and not in your satisfaction.

Roosm are small even for Parisian standards and staff is unfriendly especially Ms. Leon - you should NOT be working in the service industry. I am a Best Western Diamond Select card holder and this is not the service standard I am used to by Best Western.

It is a shame, because the location is very good and convenient with Gare Du Nord (eurostar) and the Metro styation only a short walk away.

On another occasiuon I had to amend a booking and the hotel was copmpletely inflexibleeven though I am a frequent visitor to Paris. Needless to say I will avoid this hotel at all cost on future trips and recommend the Best Western Marais Grands Boulevards or Best Western Opera which are just down the street to anyone who is thinking of staying at a Best Western in this area.

This is a great small hotel in a perfect condition. We travelled via train and it is really just a 10 minute walk from Gare du Nord to the Hotel. There is a metro stop about 1 minute away so practically on the doorstep.
The staff are extremely helpful and friendly. The hotel room was not huge but absolutely sufficient and very clean. The bed very comfortable. The bathroom was a good size with great shower.
The room we had (4th floor) had bathrobes and slippers.
We had booked the room including breakfast which was buffet style and was extremely good offering hot and cold food.
We will definitely return here to this great little hotel with the great staff.

We spent a couple of days in this hotel which has a very good location and is extremely clean with well fitted rooms. The 04 guests rooms are big and can accommodate 04 persons groups.
The breakfast is decent without being gargantuan.
A plenty of good restaurants and various stores are very close in addition to 02 train stations.

Would recommend the property for a stay in Paris. The room was clean and comfortable. The staff was excellent throughout our stay. The location is about a 30 minute walk to the Opera House for a sense of location.

If you have a suitcase and or are with 2 people I would not recommend this hotel. I have stayed in my life in hundreds of hotels but never stayed in a 4 star hotel room this small. I would suggest to look a further to find a room that has at least space for a suitcase....

If you are looking for a hotel for a couple for a night or so, this is an excellent choice. It's located within walking distance to the Montmartre, many restaurants, boulangerie and patisserie, etc. While the room was small, it was spotless and the shower was great. Very comfortable bed and very little street noise.

The location was very good, convenient and accessible, Paris Gare Du Nord is only 8 minutes walk and Poisonairre metro is less than a minute walk. very tiny rooms and the staff can do much better with helping their guestd. They couldnt find an adaptor for my American laptop and phone - I had chargers. That was really poor example of customer service, Airconditions are not working in 26 degrees temperature - I call the reception, the response I get is we dont give fresh air in october, we switch off a/c in oct because it is cold outside but it was 26 degrees. Everthing you need you have to go down to their tiny reception and ask for - cant get done by phone. They locked my access card 2 days in a row and I had to go down to get it unlocked - how frustrating after a tiring day. But as I said location wise very good. Not living to the standards of the Best Western brand.

Not good hotel don’t waste your money the location the place is not good for family plus staff very rude if u speak English that’s it u done the room is like Uk box room the breakfast place like my small kitchen man

I was initially disappointed as booking.com described the executive king with sofa bed as having a bath. Room 101 had no bath but a large, well lit wet room with great shower and mirrors (a must for make up) made up for it . Also the bath robe and slippers were non existent. Not a problem for me but daughter wasn't happy. Requested 2 adaptors but only one available at 10 euro deposit. No sofa bed but a fold up bed which did block wardrobe and coffee/kettle access when in use. Street quite noisy front of hotel so could be a problem in summer with windows open. We left the wet room window open and door closed for less noise as air vents above it. Great, thick blackout curtains. Wonderfully large, comfortable beds and pillows. Friend said folding bed could have had better mattress but was comfy enough. Crisp clean sheets. Ideal location for Gard Du Nord and Poisonniere Metro. Didn't have breakfast as late risers but so many places to eat on doorstep, even a vegan restaurant directly opposite. Friendly staff on desk 24/7. We didn't arrive back until 4 am one night so was glad this wasn't one of the many hotels in Paris where you have to hand your key in on leaving and are locked out after a certain hour. In all our stay here helped make our visit to Paris a happy, memorable, comfortable one and we would def book here again.

Very small waiting area. But extremely spacious white rooms. Im not the biggest fan of the bathroom showers but the location cant be beat. 2 min walk to the train station
15 mins to the Louvre. Check in was a 2pm. Check out is at 11am. Breakfast can be served up to your room. Huge windows. Not terrible loud

I’ve travelled to France/Europe many many times. I find it difficult to find an affordable clean hotel. I was very happy to find this one.

The bed was also very very comfortable with amazing blackout curtains.

People at reception were very kind.
The room was very small. Barely enough space on the ground to open my suitcase but I still give it 5/5

Wonderful friendly staff, especially for English speakers. Very accommodating. We loved the location, handy convenient stores near by as well as the underground metro right outside the door. Quiet and safe neighborhood. Rooms are very spacious, bed was amazing and extremely clean rooms. Would stay again!

We enjoyed our stay here. The room was small, but the king bed was enough for my husband, my daughter and myself. Most of the staff spoke English, some fluently, and it was enough for us to get everything we needed, including ordering taxis for rides, and also having food delivered. There is a/c there, but on the day we arrived, it was over 100 degrees, so the staff even added a fan in our room to help keep it cool. The room was clean and fresh and although we didn't spend much time in the room, it certainly suited our needs. If it werent for our desire to check out other places, we would return here on our next visit.

Booked our stay extremely last minute because of an Airbnb nightmare. To say the least, the stay totally changed our Paris experience and made us really comfortable each night. Clean & large bathroom. The only downside was housekeeping was not done with our room when we had reached back at 3/4pm one of the days. But apart from that, I would definitely recommend.

I have been here last week for 1 night for a quick business trip.
I received a welcome mail after booking whereas they asked for some informations/details (time of arrival, special request,etc), not too many,just the right amount, it was a nice little touch, appreciated.
I arrived around 20:00, booking was fast and professional, made a request and it was satisfied immediately, much appreciated. Room is typical smaller parisien size, nice decor, modern, good,clean and spacious bathroom with rainshower.
Air conditioned was working perfectly, welcome due to 30 & more degrees outside.
Some minor details in the bathroom coule be improuved, but the price/ service is outstanding, and the management was always efficient when needed.
Hotel itself is located just next to poissonniere subway stop, a close walk to opera, and just next to Gare du Nord et Est, Recommended.

Due to the Women's Football World-cup and other events, the room rate was unfortunately outrageous for this level of facility.
The room switch of room 104 was broken and only temporarily work when the front person hit the wall around the switch so hard.

Very tiny rooms, awful service, bad smell in loby, simple breakfast
Not recommended
Break fast room was really small and messy and when we ask them too make up, they just smile!!!
Very very tiny rooms with really bad ventilation
I was really happy to leave this 4 star!! Hotel

Everything about this hotel is pretty good apart from breakfast which was a disgrace!

The location is good being around 10 minutes from the Gare du Nord and in a quiet rosd by a metro station. The welcome was very friendly and the receptionist was really pleasant.

Rooms were reasonable sized and the beds comfortable. It was quiet and we had a good night's sleep. There are many pleasant restaurants nearby so dinner was not a problem. We were within walking distance of the Sacre Coeur so there was a lot to do nearby.

UNFORTUNATELY breakfast was terrible!

The room is too small for the hotel and when we arrived there were no free tables. The lady in charge did not help by suggesting that several tables would be free soon and showed no interest in us at all. Eventually a table for four became available so the five of us in the party sat down and borrowed a chair from another table. After a wait, the lady in charge started laying places for four even though there were five of us.

The food itself was OK but the most shocking thing was that when some other tables became empty, no-one cleared the tables and laid them again. The lady in charge chatted to her friend in the kitchen and did nothing.

When further guests arrived for breakfast they were greeted by dirty tables! It was only with great huffing and puffing that they were cleared.

And FINALLY to add insult to injury, my wife asked for another cup of breakfast tea. We had already paid 14 Euros and usually you can get a second cup of tea. NOT HERE. The lady asked my wife for a further 4 Euros. My wife speaks good French so this was clearly not a misunderstanding.

Next time we will go out to breakfast...or more likely never go back.

I stayed here twice and I will never stay here again.
The staff were good, but that's about it.
The room was clean, but the bed was at a slope, though there was a dip, so that I didn't slide all the way out the bed. The pillows were so soft that they offered no support at all.
The breakfast was basic to say the least.

The kindness and the professionalism of the personnel, the very good location walking distance from international railway station Gare du Nord and subway station Poissonniere. The breakfast is good enough. The amenities are a bit under expectation for a 4 star hotel.

Convenient location near a metro stop. Not too far out, but not too busy either. Great location for my little family to use as home base. The hotel was clean and had all the amenities we needed. Hotel service was polite and helpful. Would definitely recommend!

This hotel was ideal for an overnight business trip!
Spotless clean, rooms small but very comfortable.
Ideal location right outside the Metro!!
There are some nice restaurants around the hotel!
It is very reasonable especially if booked in advance!
Enjoy

We had executive room. Only 1 complementary bottle of water for room for 2 people! Walls super thin between rooms and no do not disturb signs and got woke By maids several times! Bathroom door needed some maintaince. Cleaning room was great. Breakfast, needs improvement pastries very small and bacon and sausages where not a great quality

The hotel is just a 7 min walk from Gare du Nord station. The room is not so big but OK. It is clean and the personnal are very helpful. The safety box in the room was broken, so I could not use that.

Everything was perfect. Great room, lovely pillows. Beautifully designed bathrooms. Very friendly concierge team. Large selection at breakfast.Would’ve liked more Pastries/Crossaints at breakfast, and more coffee/milk in room.

We have visited this hotel forum the 4th time. Dogs are allowed and used to be free of charge. Newly 10€ per dog per Day will be charged, Mrs Vanessa told us. I complained this at a very friendly collegue. She mentioned there will not be an extra charge. That is what i call customer satisfaction.

The staff was incredibly helpful and friendly. The room and lobby areas were modern, clean and well-kept, and the location was great - close to the metro and lots of things to see and do. Wouldn't change a thing!

The room was small but perfect for what we needed as we were sightseeing most of the time. The hotel was clean, the staff were friendly and helpful and it had everything we needed. I would definitely recommend to anyone looking for somewhere to stay during their city break.

Typical medium sized 4 star hotel.

Located less than 8-10 mins walk from Gare Du Nord and 15-18 mins walk to Galeries Lafayette.

The rooms were in good condition , reception helpful and a hot breakfast was served.

Excellent hôtel, clean, confortable and welcoming staff. The only problem is that you cannot use whatsapp due to security filter set up by the hotel in the internet network. This has to be improved . I stayed several times in the hotel over the last years and this problem remains

Small room (but this is Paris) but clean. Literally 2 minutes walking from the Metro and walking distance from the train station. Lots of restaurateur around. Breakfast is nice. Receptionist was helpful

we stayed for 2 nights, my missus have mobility issues and when we got to the room it was tiny. i mean you have problem moving around the double bed to the bathroom with ... weird balcony - yes you have to go via bathroom to the balcony. minimal space if yoiu have any mobility issues is a no no. I read that other rooms are big etc. but not in our case. Btw smoke alarms are very sensitive - even for shower steam so be prepared to be evacuated at 2AM in the morning. i am not joking, location is ok, close to station, uber ride few euros. but would not stay here again even tho i have their loyalty card.

We stayed there for 2 nights as we wanted to be near to Gare l'Est & Gare du Nord (arrived from London).

Pros:
1) Very friendly people at reception. Accommodating and hospitable.

2) Receptionist took the trouble to explain and even show us that the classic room which we booked, was too small for 2 nights. We really appreciated that she did that as we saw that the Classic room was REALLY TOO SMALL for 2 people. She said if you were to stay for more than a night, it would be highly recommended to upgrade to a slightly larger room for 20 Euros more a night. Thank goodness she suggested that!! We found the superior room quite small (we couldn't open our large luggage bags without it getting it in the way) but it was way better than the classic room.

3) Some nice touches in the bathroom - magnifying mirror, facial tissues, heated towel rack!

4) Hotel is literally 1 minute away from the metro Poissonniere. Extremely easy to get to other parts of Paris from here.

5) Comfy Bed.

Cons:
1) Room size is really suitable for say 1 person with a small bag, who won't spend more than a few hours in the room to just sleep. I had to do abit of work on my laptop on the table and I just found the space to be too small. I had another person in the room - and we just found the space just too cramped.

2) The table / furniture like Wardrobe in the room were pretty cheap, and you can tell it wasn't well made - e.g. the wardrobe in our room kept making sounds whenever you open / closed it which was rather irritating......

3) You could hear next door neighbours - whenever they made sounds. The rooms aren't very well sound insulated. We were this close to knocking their door to ask them to keep the noise down.

In Summary, the hotel is a small boutique hotel, there's some rooms for improvement if it wants to be anywhere near a 4 star. But all in all, it's clean, has comfortable beds and very near to the metro. If you want to be near metro poissonniere, then this is the hotel for you to stay as it's reasonably priced for what you get in the Gare Du Nord / L'Est area.

Great location, 5 min walk from Gare de Nord train station. 30 seconds from Metro with easy links to the whole of Paris, good bars/restuaraunts nearby. Room size small but comfy and great showeroom. Friendly staff on reception, plenty of choice at breakfast. Good internet conection

First, the check in was easy. The hotel location is just in the heart of the city, 1 minute away to the metro station. Many places are in walking-distance. The room was small but it was as we expected, it was clean, the bathroom was spacey enough. Every one in the receptionist are nice and helpful.

I love the room at this hotel. The super comfortable bed and good equipment. Very kind personel. Breakfast was excellent too. The location is really convenient to visit Paris. Is the center but calme. I reccomand.

This hotel has a great location if you want to travel from/to Gare du Nord! Staff are very welcoming and friendly. We were able to leave our luggage before the checkin time, which was very convenient to us.

My stay in ParisI am very happy with service I received from Best Western Primier Fabourg 88 staff. The location is great and relatively close to metro, and many favorite places of Paris, such as Louvre, sacre cour , Galeria , etc.

We chose this hotel for it's proximity to Gare du Nord as we were arriving and leaving via this station. It is ideally situated for this. Less than 10 mins walk. Location is great for access to the sights too. Metro station literally on the doorstep with direct line to the Louvre. We also caught the tourist hop on bus from Gare du Nord easily. We stayed in the Junior suite as we had 2 kids with us and the room was spacious and comfy with a large bathroom. Breakfast was sufficient and the staff friendly. Breakfast room is tiny and I imagine could get packed at busy times but they also offer the choice of having breakfast in the room. Free wifi was great. We found this hotel a refreshing change from the big chain hotels we have stayed in before. Instead it offered a boutique feel. Would stay again for sure.

The room was smaller than a shoebox hotel in New York and I didn't even have space to open my luggage in the room. Also not sure how they managed to get a 4 star rating because the place barely had any amenities or value added services, for those reasons I think the hotel is overpriced.

The staff were friendly and helpful, and location was good if you want to stay next to gare du nord (main train station) it's about a 5 minute walk.

Overall, I wouldn't want to stay there again

We stayed in a Superior Room, which despite the name is really small. You have move sideways along the foot of the bed to get to the other side.

Despite this the hotel was really good, nicely decorated and great value for money. The staff were all friendly and helpful and spoke English and it's about a 10 minute walk from Gare Du Nord.

We didn't bother with the hotel breakfasts as there is plenty of places around the hotel for food, the bakers just across the road (down the hill from the Metro) does lovely cakes and pastries and coffee that you can take away back to the room and is a two minute stroll.

The Metro is almost outside the front door of the hotel making travel around the place really easy, about a 15-20 journey to the Eiffel Tower or Champs-Élysées and even quicker to the Louvre as it's on the same line. If you're moving around quite a bit, buy the 15 ticket 'carnet' of Metro tickets for under €15.

I was visiting Paris for the first time, and I stayed at the Best Western Premier Faubourg 88. Overall, I enjoyed the experience. My Superior room was a pretty good size and didn't cost a lot. There was more than enough storage for two large suitcases and all of the things I bought while I was in the city. The bathroom was a good size too. The staff was very friendly and helpful during my stay, communicating in English as well as French. It's in a great location, just a short walk from Gare du Nord, and a few steps from the Poissoniere metro station (which was also a plus, since I walked a lot during my trip and didn't feel like walking all the way back to my room most days!) The neighborhood is nice and quiet as well, and there are also many good restaurants and stores nearby (though quite a few were closed while I was there, as it was the August holidays when almost everyone leaves town). I would highly recommend this hotel, especially if you are visiting Paris for the first time and want a nice room for a great value.

This hotel has the tiniest rooms I've ever seen (you have to walk sideways to get around the bed in some of them) but the service was really helpful and the breakfast is one of the best rates you'll get for a petit dejeneur in Paris.

Location wise, this hotel is in the middle of a lot of stuff but near nothing. You're pretty much equidistant to the Louvre and Montmartre, but that's a solid 20-30 min walk depending on your speed.

My friend had to leave early and when she explained that she'd been robbed multiple times in Italy and just wanted to go home, they refunded her. Great, understanding people.

We wanted a hotel near Gare du nord as we arrived by Eurostar, this was just a 5 minute walk. The metro is just at the end of the street and there are some lovely cafe's & restaurants nearby. The room we had was a superior twin room which was clean and adequate size for us, we were only there to sleep after all. Only downside was it was noisy outside but then we were in a capital city so expected. Breakfast was basic but enough for us, as we are not big morning eaters. Staff were very friendly and the street/metro map at reception was very handy. We would come again and recommend for short stays.

June 18th, me, my wife, and 16-year-old son stayed at the Best Western Hotel Premier Faubourg 88 for 2 nights + 1 at Holiday Inn. We booked through Trip Masters. Our room was not ready on the day we had booked so we were routed to the Holiday Inn Paris- Gare de I'Est. for the first night and then we were transferred back to the Best Western the day after. This was an inconvenience since we did not have access to a room during the times they were cleaned but the Holiday Inn was a nicer hotel. The Best Western was clean and the staff were polite but the room was very small. We are average sized people but I can tell you that this hotel is not suitable for anyone larger. Air conditioning was excellent and beds were comfortable. Maid service was good. A very limited breakfast is offered for an additional charge of 7 to 9 euros each in a very cramped room. There are a number of expensive cafes within walking distance which seemed to all serve basically the same thing. See my review on a much better choice from last year at the Novotel Suites Paris Expo Porte de Versailles.

Like most hotels in Paris, it is nice, super expensive and I don’t think it would match the equivalent 4 stars anywhere else.

Service is good and helpful but like you would get in such a small hotel.

Rooms are very nice though and worth seeing.

Short walk from Gare du Nord Train station and metro station is less than 1 block. Surprisingly quiet, very little noise. Very modern, clean and nice with air conditioning! Wonderful coffee shops and restaurants within 5-10 minute walk from this hotel.

Stayed for 2 nights on a business trip.

Short walk from Gare du Nord, no more than 10min walk

Very modern and well sized rooms vs some hotels of a similar class that are quite old fashioned

And a real bonus is air conditioning! Many hotels so they have it but they don’t, it’s just a fan in the room.

I had a street facing room, bar some street noise which is the norm in Paris v quiet at night as the hotel is just off the main road.

You have many great coffee spots and eateries on your doorstop. I’d higly recommend Marlette for breakfast - same price as the hotel but proper artisan coffee and great food.

Also a 10min walk to hipster central Rue Faubourg - where of an evening you are spoilt for choice with bars and food.

This is one of the best hotels I’ve stayed in for business given the price of this hotel.

Within 100 geet of Patisserie for croissants and more.. Grocery store next door.

Small room, small bathroom, (bring your own soap) resembling more a small cruise ship cabin.

Good for two or three day stay. Good breakfast

Friendly helpful checkin staff !

Safe hotel, safe area. We used Uber to get around, they come within 3 minutes. 45 euros to CDG airport.

I would stay there again.

The location is good, room was clean but extremely small; we could hardly walk around the bed to go to the bathroom. Air conditioning wasn't working and we had to open the windows which was right on a very noisy street, difficult to sleep. The best part of this hotel was the front desk, they all were very helpful, kind and professional, specially a lady called

Good :-

Very well located for Gare du Nord and Poissonnière Metro station. Walkable to Pigalle, Montmatre

Staff were friendly and helpful

Comfortable bed, clean room

Quiet in terms of external noise

Bad :-

They let guests smoke in the centre courtyard, it even seems to be encouraged with the provision of an ashtray. However, this means if you have your window open you get a room full of cigarette smoke - not pleasant.

We used the provided teabags on day one and they were not refilled for the rest of our stay

The switch that was meant to turn the light off in the wardrobe was badly fitted so closing the door did not activate it so the light stayed on all night

The BBC News channel (50) did not work so had to suffer CNN when needed my news fix :(

Not particularly quiet in terms of internal noise, you can hear wardrobe doors being closed in other room and especially toilets being flushed

To summarise I seem to have more negative points than positive but this is a nice hotel and the location is well worth considering it for

Our room was clean and quiet. As the road in the front of the hotel is not very busy, there is almost no traffic noise at night. The staff was very friendly and helpful. There are a lot of good restaurants around the hotel. The Metro station is just a few steps away. We enjoyed it a lot.
